Parents,

Please look early this next week for an email containing a direct certification letter and directions if your are in a food assistance program or other government programs that may allow you to get free or reduced lunches. If you receive this letter we need this turned back in on or before August 11. If you do receive a letter do not fill out a free and reduced application on the registration site. Your fees have already been reduced accordingly and you are already eligible for free or reduced meals.

If you don't receive a letter but think you might qualify please fill out the application online when available later next week. I will notify you if you are eligible and change your fees and lunch status accordingly.

The registration site will open sometime next week. Notice will go out in the papers and Facebook also.

Thank you for being patient and working on this for us.

Mr. Kronemann

post_text:
West Hancock Schools is proud to partner with the Hancock County Foundation. This year they graciously allowed us to alter our original grant request to help the school secure wireless internet access hot spots. We were able to provide these hot spots to student's who were without internet access during the COVID-19 closure. With these supports we were able to make sure that all of our students received equitable access to their education. We couldn't have done this without their support.

The Hancock County Foundation has been a tremendous resource for our school and community. To learn more about who they are and what they do, please check them out through this link https://www.desmoinesfoundation.org/affiliates/hancock-county

post_text:
Here are a couple of announcements regarding some activities at West Hancock High School.

1. Graduation and Awards Night are back on with live in-person ceremonies for the students! Unfortunately, graduation will not be open to the public due to seating concerns that we need to maintain social distancing with. With that in mind KIOW/KHAM will be live streaming our graduation ceremony through their website.
a. Awards Ceremony will be Wednesday, June 10th at 6 PM
b. Graduation will be Sunday, June 14th at 2 PM (the public is encouraged attend only via live streaming online)

2. Summer Sports are on! Baseball and Softball games will start June 15th. The games will be open to the public however social distancing is still enforced. This means we will not be able to provide any bleacher seating and we won’t be able to provide a concession stand. For more information, please visit the state association website. https://www.iahsaa.org/wp-content/uploads/2020/05/Iowa-DE-Guidance-Summer-Sports-5.20.20.pdf

post_text:
Due to the COVID-19 school closure, West Hancock Community School District will pre register preschool students for the 2020-2021 school year through an online registration link found on the district website. Information regarding important details about our 3-year and 4-year old preschool programs will also be available on the district's website. The pre registration link will be available on April 15.

Children must be 3 or 4 years old by September 15, 2020 to be eligible for preschool. Parents will finalize registration in August and will be asked to provide a copy of the child's birth certificate and immunization records at that time. Due to the unusual circumstances, section preference and enrollment into 3 year old preschool will be based on the order that pre registration information is submitted online.

shared_text:
West Hancock Community Schools added 25 new photos.
March 20 at 11:01 AM ·

On March 13th, Mrs. Tremmel's math classes celebrated Pi Day (March 14). The Pre-Algebra and Algebra 1 classes created Pi art by using different colors to represent each digit 0-9, then used those colors to go from the first digit of Pi to the next, to the next, etc. to make a beautiful art piece based on the digits of Pi. The Algebra 2 classes explored how Archimedes first approximated Pi. They drew inscribed and circumscribed polygons in and around a circle to get an upper and lower bound for the circumference of the circle. Archimedes eventually used a 96-sided polygon, but that would be a lot to draw so we stopped at 16! The Advanced Math and Calculus classes got a chance to eat some pie! Then they watched some videos about the special number and discussed how it is used in real life! It was a fun day to celebrate such an important number!

Preregistration for 2020-2021 school year for kprep and kindergarten is being held at the West Hancock Elementary School on Thursday, March 26. Children must be 5 years old by September 15, 2020 to be eligible for kprep or kindergarten. Parents are asked to bring a copy of the child's birth certificate and immunization records if not already on file.

The informational meeting begins at 6:30 pm. Doors open at 6:00 pm for preregistration. This meeting is designed for parents only.

If you have any questions, please call West Hancock Elementary at 843-3833.

West Hancock Community Schools added 9 new photos — in Britt, Iowa.
March 3 at 5:41 PM · Britt, IA ·

Imagine being given the task, where you need to invent a machine to show a sign or complete a circuit. That is what is happened in the fourth-grade classes of Mrs. HIldman and Mrs. Kahlstorf. They came down to the high school two weeks ago and saw the machines that Ms. Carlson’s physics class built and took to the Engineering Machine Design Competition that was held at St. Ansgar. So today, the physics students went to the fourth-grade classrooms and saw their machines. What a tremendous learning experience!

post_text:
Congratulations to Ms. Carlson and her Physics students in representing West Hancock so well in the annual Engineering Design Competition. Our team of Mahayla Faust, Emily Ryerson, Riley Hiscocks, Maddie Eisenman, and Amanda Chizek qualified for the Midwest Regional Championships!

Many thanks to the Cobbler Shoppe and Jay Hiscocks - State Farm Insurance for sponsoring and funding this event for us!

Below is a brief write up of the competition. In the attached images you'll see the full two page document of the press release for this event.

On Monday, February 17th, 2020 St. Ansgar High School hosted the 2nd annual Engineering Design Competition in conjunction with the Minnesota State Engineering Center. This event was the second ever official Engineering Design contest
held in the state of Iowa. This competition originated on the east coast. This year the top 4 teams and the People’s choice award will have the opportunity to compete in the Midwest Championships that will be hosted by the Minnesota Twins in early May. The winning team will even be able to throw out the first pitch!

post_text:
Give back to West Hancock CSD with Casey’s Rewards

We’re excited to share that our district is participating in Cash for Classrooms, part of Casey’s Rewards. This opens up each of the buildings in the district to new funding opportunities to help improve learning environments for students.
The best part? Donations don’t come out of your own pocket. When you buy from Casey’s and use their rewards program you can simply turn your points into a donation to our school.
Help West Hancock CSD make the most of this program and learn more at Caseys.com/schools.

Give back to West Hancock CSD with Casey’s Rewards

We’re excited to share that our district is participating in Cash for Classrooms, part of Casey’s Rewards. This opens up each of the buildings in the district to new funding opportunities to help improve learning environments for students.
The best part? Donations don’t come out of your own pocket. When you buy from Casey’s and use their rewards program you can simply turn your points into a donation to our school.
Help West Hancock CSD make the most of this program and learn more at Caseys.com/schools.

CASEYS.COM
Casey's Rewards Cash for Classrooms | Casey's General Stores

post_text:
Happy Holidays and thank you for a wonderful Fine Arts celebration week from the West Hancock Mixed Chorus!

The WH Mixed Chorus members have been busy performing in many events already this year. Anthems at most home athletic events, a fall concert, NCICDA Honor Choir, winter concert, and Electos even performed the anthem at football playoffs! Not to mention the upcoming Note-able (pops) concert, anthem for the North Iowa Bulls in February, spring concert, large group and so much more!

There is no better way to lift your spirits and bring people together than choral music.
"When words fail, music speaks." Hans Christian Anderson

post_text:
Happy Fine Arts Week from the West Hancock Theatre Department!

Drama fun fact: Did you know that we owe these sayings to William Shakespeare? "Knock, knock! Who's there?", "Heart of gold", "Good riddance", "Send him packing", "Bated breath", "Vanish into thin air", "Makes your hair stand on end", "Wild goose chase", "Break the ice", and many more!

Pictured are shots from this fall's murder mystery "Til Death Do Us Part" written by Craig Sodaro and directed by Sharayah Hacker

post_text:
Updated - collecting Thursday and Saturday this week.

Attention high school athletes and fans, our West Hancock TAG Program is partnering with the Pajama Project to provide a good night’s sleep to children in need in our area. We are asking for a warm pair of pajamas, a bedtime story, or cash donations at two of our next home events. We are going to have collection boxes in place at the H.S. band and choir concert on Thursday 12/19, and the wrestling tournament on December 21. Donations are not required, however, they are encouraged and will be used to benefit the children in our communities. There will be donation boxes in place near the entrance. Thank you in advance for your love and support of the Pajama Project.

Sincerely, the West Hancock TAG Program.

post_text: The West Hancock High School Chemistry class has been studying stoichiometry. Stoichiometry is the study of quantitative relationships in chemical reactions. The students were given two solutions and they had to determine the products when the two are mixed together. They also had to determine the balanced equation for the reaction that took place.
